  "notes": [
    "Schedule C (Form 1040) AcroForm widget map for the IRS-hosted TY2025 PDF (PDF /Title metadata: '2025 Schedule C (Form 1040)').",
    "TY2024-vs-TY2025 deltas: line 27 was split into 27a (Other expenses, the Layer 1 field) and 27b (Energy efficient commercial buildings deduction \u00a7179D). Layer 1 ScheduleCFields carries only 27a; the 27b widget f1_39[0] is unmapped. Sum line 28 still includes both 27a and 27b on the IRS form.",
    "Schedule C Part II expense lines 8-27a are laid out in TWO columns: lines 8-17 in the LEFT column (x ~194-294), lines 18-27b in the RIGHT column (x ~475-576). The IRS f-number sequence INTERLEAVES left-col and right-col widgets in a non-monotonic way (e.g. f1_28 is line 18, f1_17 is line 8, f1_22 is line 13, f1_33 is line 22). The map is keyed by the semantic Layer 1 field name so callers do NOT need to know the f-number ordering.",
    "Line 27a is f1_40[0], not f1_39[0]. f1_39[0] is line 27b energy efficient buildings deduction.",
    "Part V 'Other Expenses' detail is a 9-row table on page 2 (lines 48 description). The map exposes it via `part_v_other_expenses_widgets` arrays so Layer 2 can iterate. Rows beyond index 8 require an attached statement (continuation).",
    "Line F (accounting method) is a RADIO group of three checkboxes (Cash/Accrual/Other). The Layer 1 string 'cash'/'accrual'/'other' selects exactly one. The 'Other (specify)' text widget f1_9 is unmapped.",
    "Line 43 vehicle placed-in-service date is split across THREE date widgets (month/day/year). Layer 1 stores a single string; the renderer must split mm/dd/yy across f2_9, f2_10, f2_11.",
    "Multi-business dispatch: Layer 2 produces ONE filled PDF per ScheduleC on the return (`render_schedule_c_pdfs_all`). Each fill is independent and uses this same widget map."
  ],
